This paper discusses the efficiency of information networks in social media, which involves analyzing user behavior and information flow. This topic falls under the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper specifically focuses on Twitter, which is a social media platform, and uses computational methods to analyze user behavior, which aligns with the topics covered in these sub-categories.
